<inglise> Notified bodies linked to a manufacturer </inglise>
<eesti> Tootjaga seotud registreeritud asutused </eesti>
<inglise> (a) The Guide (Fiche II/B IV) states "Notified bodies are and must remain third parties. </inglise>
<eesti> a) Juhend (alajaotus II/B IV) sisaldab j&auml;rgmist s&auml;tet: "Registreeritud asutused on kolmas osapool ja peavad selleks j&auml;&auml;ma. </eesti>
<inglise> As third parties they should remain independent of their clients and other interested parties </inglise>
<eesti> Kolmanda osapoolena peavad nad j&auml;&auml;ma s&otilde;ltumatuks oma klientidest ja teistest huvitatud pooltest </eesti>
<inglise> .... Facilities such as laboratories or inspectorates owned by economic operators (first or seconnd parties) cannot be notified separately". </inglise>
<eesti> .... Selliste &uuml;ksuste kohta nagu ettev&otilde;tjatele (esimene v&otilde;i teine osapool) kuuluvad laborid v&otilde;i inspektsioonid ei saa esitada eraldi teatist." </eesti>
<inglise> For these reasons it is considered that certification and inspection bodies that are not separate legal entities cannot be notified under the CPD. </inglise>
